{
  "FLOKE-Site-update-1--June-2026-06-01": {
    "path": "FLOKE-Site-update-1--June-2026-06-01",
    "url": "https://telegra.ph/FLOKE-Site-update-1--June-2026-06-01",
    "title": "FLOKE Site update #1 · June 2026",
    "description": "Echo\nThe first Floke Engine game is live on the site. Pixel space shooter, runs in the browser without install. Not a teaser, not a coming soon placeholder — an actual playable first title. The same pixel space backdrop you see in the screenshots is the game itself. Move, shoot, survive.\nThis is what Floke Engine means in practice: small games that ship, not decks about games that might ship someday.\nEaster eggs\nA few secrets are hidden around the site. Pixel editor — draw 16×16 art, export with or without…",
    "author_name": "Floke Studio",
    "author_url": "https://t.me/flokestudio",
    "image_url": "https://i.postimg.cc/02d9zkPn/Gemini-Generated-Image-opxkr6opxkr6opxk.png",
    "content": [
      {
        "tag": "figure",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "img",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "https://i.postimg.cc/02d9zkPn/Gemini-Generated-Image-opxkr6opxkr6opxk.png"
            }
          },
          {
            "tag": "figcaption",
            "children": [
              "Floke Engine"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Echo"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "The first Floke Engine game is live on the site. Pixel space shooter, runs in the browser without install. Not a teaser, not a coming soon placeholder — an actual playable first title. The same pixel space backdrop you see in the screenshots is the game itself. Move, shoot, survive."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "This is what Floke Engine means in practice: small games that ship, not decks about games that might ship someday."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Easter eggs"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "A few secrets are hidden around the site. Pixel editor — draw 16×16 art, export with or without a FLOKE frame. Pilot portrait — 8×8, shows up in Echo runs. Something else too. We're not going to list them. Find them."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Themes"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Dark, light, paper, pink, CRT mode. Each one changes the whole feel of the site — not just colors, the grain, the glow, the contrast. Paper feels like reading on a warm afternoon. CRT feels like 1994. Pink is what it is."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Switch them in the nav. Pick your default."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Command Palette"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Hit ",
          {
            "tag": "code",
            "children": [
              "/"
            ]
          },
          " or ",
          {
            "tag": "code",
            "children": [
              "Cmd+K"
            ]
          },
          " anywhere on the site. Search products, jump to sections, switch themes, open pages. Keyboard-first navigation for people who prefer not to scroll."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Comments"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Leave feedback directly through GitHub — no separate account, no third-party form. It's there, at the bottom of the page. Say something if you want."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Product graph"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "An interactive map of the Floke ecosystem — products, engines, connections. Drag nodes. See how Glyph connects to Senza. See where Flint fits. It's not a diagram in a doc, it lives on the page."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Origin Timeline"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "How Floke started. One developer, a few ideas, a decision to keep things local. It's a short read at the bottom of the About section."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "hr"
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Release #1 is out — full notes on Telegraph with everything Senza and Cultiva shipped this month. The site update is separate: it's not a product release, it's a place that got better overnight."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "More coming in July."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "→ ",
          {
            "tag": "a",
            "attrs": {
              "href": "https://flokestudio.github.io/Floke/",
              "target": "_blank"
            },
            "children": [
              "flokestudio.github.io/Floke"
            ]
          },
          " → ",
          {
            "tag": "a",
            "attrs": {
              "href": "/FLOKE-Release-1--Iyun-2026-05-31"
            },
            "children": [
              "Full release #1 on Telegraph"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "views": 4
  },
  "FLOKE-Release-1--Iyun-2026-05-31": {
    "path": "FLOKE-Release-1--Iyun-2026-05-31",
    "url": "https://telegra.ph/FLOKE-Release-1--Iyun-2026-05-31",
    "title": "FLOKE Release #1 · June 2026",
    "description": "Floke",
    "image_url": "https://i.postimg.cc/5NqGS39s/Untitled.jpg",
    "content": [
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Floke"
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "figure",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "img",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "https://i.postimg.cc/5NqGS39s/Untitled.jpg"
            }
          },
          {
            "tag": "figcaption",
            "children": [
              "Release #1"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Floke Studio"
            ]
          },
          " is a lineup of apps that ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "live on your computer"
            ]
          },
          ". Music, habits, metadata — later, local agents. No mandatory cloud. No account just to open the app. We’re not anti-internet — MusicBrainz and search in Flint will stay optional. But the core is always offline-first: your files, your library, your garden."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Release #1"
            ]
          },
          " is the first month ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Senza"
            ]
          },
          " and ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Cultiva"
            ]
          },
          " ship ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "together"
            ]
          },
          " — one post, one rhythm. Before, each product had its own date. Going forward, we want a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "monthly"
            ]
          },
          " update you can expect and a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "yearly"
            ]
          },
          " big version. No magic promises — just a calendar that makes sense."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "June codenames: ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Legato"
            ]
          },
          " — music that doesn’t snap between tracks. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Cypress"
            ]
          },
          " — a calm, “forest” Cultiva release. Below — what changed and why."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "hr"
      },
      {
        "tag": "h3",
        "attrs": {
          "id": "Senza-feels-alive"
        },
        "children": [
          "Senza feels alive"
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "figure",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "img",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "https://i.postimg.cc/g2GTrZpr/image.png"
            }
          },
          {
            "tag": "figcaption",
            "children": [
              "Flow"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Senza used to ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "store"
            ]
          },
          " and ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "play"
            ]
          },
          " music. That’s not enough if you listen to ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "albums"
            ]
          },
          ", not random files from search. There was silence between tracks — small, but noticeable every time. In ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "1.1.0 Legato"
            ]
          },
          " we closed the gap between a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "library manager"
            ]
          },
          " and a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "real player"
            ]
          },
          "."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Crossfade"
            ]
          },
          " — tracks ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "flow"
            ]
          },
          " into each other instead of hard cuts. Zero to eight seconds: some want a barely visible seam, some want a long handoff like a live set. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Shuffle"
            ]
          },
          " and ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "repeat"
            ]
          },
          " (playlist or one track) — hard to live without on a big library. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Hotkeys"
            ]
          },
          " — Space, arrows, M, L — and ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "media keys"
            ]
          },
          " on your keyboard: play/pause on a laptop without the mouse. Everything you expect from a player, finally here, next to Flow and Vault."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Why this matters for Floke: Senza isn’t “another streaming clone.” It’s ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "your"
            ]
          },
          " collection on disk. The player should respect it the way streaming respects its queue — minus subscription and minus sending plays to a server."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Lyrics"
            ]
          },
          " from a sidecar ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "code",
                "children": [
                  ".lrc"
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          " file (next to the track) show ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "in the player"
            ]
          },
          ", line by line, in sync. No separate lyrics site — all local."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Favorites"
            ]
          },
          " — a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "heart"
            ]
          },
          " on the track and a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "dedicated sidebar"
            ]
          },
          " view. Flow’s ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "“Favorites”"
            ]
          },
          " mode follows those marks: your choice, not “we think you’ll like this.” ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Recently played"
            ]
          },
          " — its own list: back to yesterday’s album in two clicks."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Glyph2.2-O"
            ]
          },
          " — our metadata layer inside Senza — now writes tags not only to ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "MP3"
            ]
          },
          " but ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FLAC, OGG, M4A, AAC, WAV"
            ]
          },
          ". Import lossless — you’re not stuck with empty fields. On add, ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "BPM"
            ]
          },
          " is computed: helps the player and genre hints in ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Glyph 2.2-O"
            ]
          },
          ". Version ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "2.2-O"
            ]
          },
          " shows in ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Flow, Vault, and Settings"
            ]
          },
          " — you always know which “brain” is inside."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Smart playlists"
            ]
          },
          " build themselves from ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "simple rules"
            ]
          },
          ": ",
          {
            "tag": "em",
            "children": [
              "not played lately"
            ]
          },
          ", ",
          {
            "tag": "em",
            "children": [
              "recently added"
            ]
          },
          ", ",
          {
            "tag": "em",
            "children": [
              "favorites only"
            ]
          },
          ". Not an engagement algorithm — honest filters on ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "your"
            ]
          },
          " history on ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "your"
            ]
          },
          " disk."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "A ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "watched folder"
            ]
          },
          " — drop a file there (or download into it) — Senza ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "picks it up"
            ]
          },
          " and adds it to the library. Handy when music lives in Downloads or a shared “Incoming” folder. Moving PCs — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "code",
                "children": [
                  "senza-library.zip"
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          ": export and import the whole structure in settings, without hand-copying thousands of paths."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Search forgives typos. The sidebar can be ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "reordered and trimmed"
            ]
          },
          ". ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Accent color"
            ]
          },
          " — not only Floke gold: pick yours if the player should feel visually ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "yours"
            ]
          },
          "."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Flow"
            ]
          },
          " — a personal wave of ~32 tracks without repeats per session: discovery, rare stuff, favorites. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Vault"
            ]
          },
          " — tag scan, duplicates, batch fill with a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "diff before apply"
            ]
          },
          ": see what will change, then Apply. You can ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "turn Glyph off"
            ]
          },
          " and keep a plain editor — we don’t force “smart” where you only want music."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Senza was Windows-only for a long time. In ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "1.1.0"
            ]
          },
          " we added ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "macOS"
            ]
          },
          " and ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Linux"
            ]
          },
          " builds — on GitHub Releases, next to installer and portable. One codebase, one idea: ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "your machine, your library"
            ]
          },
          "."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Download Senza →"
            ]
          },
          " ",
          {
            "tag": "a",
            "attrs": {
              "href": "https://github.com/FlokeStudio/Senza/releases/latest",
              "target": "_blank"
            },
            "children": [
              "https://github.com/FlokeStudio/Senza/releases/latest"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "hr"
      },
      {
        "tag": "h3",
        "attrs": {
          "id": "Cultiva-is-yours"
        },
        "children": [
          "Cultiva is yours"
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "figure",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "img",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "https://i.postimg.cc/rwYNc0wX/image.png"
            }
          },
          {
            "tag": "figcaption",
            "children": [
              "Garden"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Cultiva"
            ]
          },
          " is a habit tracker that grows ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "visually"
            ]
          },
          ": seed, sprout, tree. No streak anxiety, no “you lost 47 days — start over.” A calm rhythm beats a red banner."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "1.1.0 Cypress"
            ]
          },
          " is about ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "mood"
            ]
          },
          ". New ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Cypress"
            ]
          },
          " theme: deep evergreen, not acid gamification. Three ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "ambient backgrounds"
            ]
          },
          " — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Cypress Drift"
            ]
          },
          ", ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Morning Dew"
            ]
          },
          ", ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Canopy Sunbeam"
            ]
          },
          " — move slowly behind the UI, like weather outside the window. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Accent color"
            ]
          },
          " and background ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "intensity"
            ]
          },
          " adjust separately: keep the atmosphere, make it barely visible."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Why this matters for Floke: habits are daily. The UI shouldn’t shout. It should ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "invite you to open the garden"
            ]
          },
          " in the morning, not shame you at night."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "When habits pile up, you need ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "search"
            ]
          },
          " — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Ctrl+F"
            ]
          },
          " in the garden, no scrolling through screens. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Hotkeys"
            ]
          },
          ": new habit, mark done, settings, dismiss — so your hands don’t live on the mouse every ten seconds."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "ZIP export"
            ]
          },
          " — habits and settings in ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "one archive"
            ]
          },
          ". Backup before an update, move to another PC, or “put on disk and forget.” Cultiva data ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "doesn’t go to our server"
            ]
          },
          " — there is no server. Only you."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Cultiva is now officially part of Floke Studio"
            ]
          },
          " — shared About, GitHub links, the same monthly rhythm as Senza. One brand, one idea: ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "tools you can trust because they don’t ask for extra"
            ]
          },
          "."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Download Cultiva →"
            ]
          },
          " ",
          {
            "tag": "a",
            "attrs": {
              "href": "https://github.com/FlokeStudio/Cultiva/releases/latest",
              "target": "_blank"
            },
            "children": [
              "https://github.com/FlokeStudio/Cultiva/releases/latest"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "hr"
      },
      {
        "tag": "h3",
        "attrs": {
          "id": "Why-Floke-exists"
        },
        "children": [
          "Why Floke exists"
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "We build software for people who want to ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "own their data"
            ]
          },
          " — music, habits, files, later — talks with local agents. Not because “cloud is evil,” but because ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "by default"
            ]
          },
          " everything should work ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "at home"
            ]
          },
          ": fast, no login, no monthly fee to open what you already downloaded."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Release #1"
            ]
          },
          " isn’t the end — it’s the ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "start of a calendar"
            ]
          },
          ". Senza and Cultiva are ready for daily use today. Next — monthly patches, ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Flint"
            ]
          },
          " in ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Q3 2026"
            ]
          },
          ", news on ",
          {
            "tag": "a",
            "attrs": {
              "href": "https://flokestudio.github.io/Floke/",
              "target": "_blank"
            },
            "children": [
              "flokestudio.github.io/Floke"
            ]
          },
          ". If it clicks, you stay with an ecosystem that doesn’t inflate for investor slides."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "hr"
      },
      {
        "tag": "h3",
        "attrs": {
          "id": "Ahead-—-Flint"
        },
        "children": [
          "Ahead — Flint"
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "br"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "The next big step — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Flint"
            ]
          },
          ". Not another ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "AI chat"
            ]
          },
          " in a browser, but a ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "desktop with local agents"
            ]
          },
          " on your computer."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "You state a task. The agent proposes ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "file edits"
            ]
          },
          ", searches the web, writes code. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Every step on screen."
            ]
          },
          " Every disk or URL action — only after your ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "yes"
            ]
          },
          " or ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "no"
            ]
          },
          ". No cloud by default. No subscription “for the model.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Agent modes: ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FliCode"
            ]
          },
          " — code and architecture. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FliWriter"
            ]
          },
          " — text. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FliWeb"
            ]
          },
          " — search and browser. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FliDocs"
            ]
          },
          " — files. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FliSlides"
            ]
          },
          " — presentations. ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "FliAgent"
            ]
          },
          " — general mode on your PC."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          "Under the hood — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Mnemo 1.2-O"
            ]
          },
          ", local inference. Not a ChatGPT proxy — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "a model on your hardware"
            ]
          },
          ". When an agent wants to ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "touch a file"
            ]
          },
          ", it stops and ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "waits for permission"
            ]
          },
          ". Same as Floke with music and habits: ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "your “okay” first"
            ]
          },
          "."
        ]
      },
      {
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "Q3 2026."
            ]
          },
          " Goal — ",
          {
            "tag": "strong",
            "children": [
              "on your machine from first launch"
            ]
          },
          ". Details in upcoming Releases."
        ]
